**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- No `X-Frame-Options` or `Content-Security-Policy` allows clickjacking attacks via iframes.
- No `Content-Security-Policy` means any future XSS bug becomes far more powerful (inline scripts, external JS allowed).
- Missing headers like `X-Content-Type-Options` and `Referrer-Policy` increase the blast radius of other bugs (content sniffing, information leakage).

