No, checking only for POST requests leaves your application vulnerable to HTTP verb tampering attacks. Attackers can bypass your security checks by using unexpected HTTP methods like HEAD, PUT, DELETE, or even custom verbs.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
<?php
require_once 'config.php';

class AdminController {
    private $pdo;

    public function __construct($pdo) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
    }

    public function deleteUser() {
        // VULNERABLE: Only checks for POST, ignores other methods
        if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'POST') {
            $this->requireAdmin();
        }

        // Attacker can use HEAD, PUT, or custom verb to skip auth
        $userId = $_REQUEST['user_id'];

        $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare("DELETE FROM users WHERE id = ?");
        $stmt->execute([$userId]);

        echo json_encode(['success' => true, 'message' => 'User deleted']);
    }

    private function requireAdmin() {
        session_start();
        if (!isset($_SESSION['is_admin']) || $_SESSION['is_admin'] !== true) {
            http_response_code(403);
            die(json_encode(['error' => 'Admin access required']));
        }
    }
}

$controller = new AdminController($pdo);
$controller->deleteUser();
```

**Attack Payload**:
```bash
# Bypass authentication using HEAD method
curl -X HEAD "https://example.com/admin/delete_user.php?user_id=1"

# Bypass using custom HTTP verb
curl -X FOOBAR "https://example.com/admin/delete_user.php" -d "user_id=1"

# Bypass using OPTIONS method
curl -X OPTIONS "https://example.com/admin/delete_user.php" -d "user_id=1"
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Security check only triggers for POST requests, allowing other methods to bypass
- HEAD requests execute the same code but don't return body (action still happens)
- Custom HTTP verbs are often not handled by security frameworks
- $_REQUEST combines GET, POST, and COOKIE data, accepting parameters from any source

**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
require_once 'config.php';

class AdminController {
    private $pdo;
    private $allowedMethods = ['POST', 'DELETE'];

    public function __construct($pdo) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
    }

    public function deleteUser() {
        // SECURE: Validate HTTP method first (whitelist approach)
        $this->validateHttpMethod();

        // SECURE: Always require authentication regardless of method
        $this->requireAdmin();

        // SECURE: Validate CSRF token
        $this->validateCsrfToken();

        // SECURE: Use $_POST only, not $_REQUEST
        $userId = filter_input(INPUT_POST, 'user_id', FILTER_VALIDATE_INT);

        if ($userId === false || $userId === null) {
            http_response_code(400);
            die(json_encode(['error' => 'Invalid user ID']));
        }

        try {
            $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare("DELETE FROM users WHERE id = ?");
            $stmt->execute([$userId]);

            $this->logAction('delete_user', $userId);
            echo json_encode(['success' => true, 'message' => 'User deleted']);
        } catch (PDOException $e) {
            error_log("Database error: " . $e->getMessage());
            http_response_code(500);
            die(json_encode(['error' => 'Internal server error']));
        }
    }

    private function validateHttpMethod() {
        $method = $_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'];

        if (!in_array($method, $this->allowedMethods, true)) {
            http_response_code(405);
            header('Allow: ' . implode(', ', $this->allowedMethods));
            die(json_encode(['error' => 'Method not allowed']));
        }
    }

    private function requireAdmin() {
        session_start();
        if (!isset($_SESSION['is_admin']) || $_SESSION['is_admin'] !== true) {
            http_response_code(403);
            $this->logAction('unauthorized_access_attempt', null);
            die(json_encode(['error' => 'Admin access required']));
        }
    }

    private function validateCsrfToken() {
        $token = $_POST['csrf_token'] ?? '';
        if (!hash_equals($_SESSION['csrf_token'] ?? '', $token)) {
            http_response_code(403);
            die(json_encode(['error' => 'Invalid CSRF token']));
        }
    }

    private function logAction($action, $targetId) {
        error_log(sprintf(
            "[AUDIT] Action: %s | User: %s | Target: %s | IP: %s | Time: %s",
            $action,
            $_SESSION['user_id'] ?? 'unknown',
            $targetId ?? 'N/A',
            $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'],
            date('Y-m-d H:i:s')
        ));
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **HTTP method whitelist**: Explicitly allow only expected methods (POST, DELETE), reject all others with 405 status
- **Authentication before action**: requireAdmin() is called unconditionally, not within a method check
- **Strict input source**: Use $_POST instead of $_REQUEST to prevent parameter injection via GET/COOKIE
- **CSRF protection**: Validate anti-CSRF tokens for state-changing operations

Implementing HTTP verb protection at the framework level ensures consistent security across all routes. Here's a production-ready middleware approach that handles verb tampering, method override attacks, and provides comprehensive logging.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```php
<?php
namespace App\Middleware;

use Psr\Http\Message\ResponseInterface;
use Psr\Http\Message\ServerRequestInterface;
use Psr\Http\Server\MiddlewareInterface;
use Psr\Http\Server\RequestHandlerInterface;
use Psr\Log\LoggerInterface;

class HttpMethodSecurityMiddleware implements MiddlewareInterface {

    private LoggerInterface $logger;
    private array $config;

    // Standard safe HTTP methods (idempotent)
    private const SAFE_METHODS = ['GET', 'HEAD', 'OPTIONS'];

    // All allowed HTTP methods (strict whitelist)
    private const ALLOWED_METHODS = [
        'GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'PATCH', 'DELETE', 'HEAD', 'OPTIONS'
    ];

    // Methods that MUST NOT have body processed
    private const BODYLESS_METHODS = ['GET', 'HEAD', 'OPTIONS', 'TRACE'];

    public function __construct(LoggerInterface $logger, array $config = []) {
        $this->logger = $logger;
        $this->config = array_merge([
            'block_method_override' => true,
            'block_custom_methods' => true,
            'log_suspicious_requests' => true,
            'enforce_content_type' => true,
        ], $config);
    }

    public function process(
        ServerRequestInterface $request,
        RequestHandlerInterface $handler
    ): ResponseInterface {

        $method = strtoupper($request->getMethod());
        $originalMethod = $method;

        // DEFENSE 1: Block unknown/custom HTTP methods
        if ($this->config['block_custom_methods']) {
            if (!in_array($method, self::ALLOWED_METHODS, true)) {
                $this->logSecurityEvent('blocked_custom_method', $request, [
                    'method' => $method
                ]);
                return $this->createErrorResponse(405, 'Method Not Allowed');
            }
        }

        // DEFENSE 2: Block HTTP method override attempts
        if ($this->config['block_method_override']) {
            $overrideAttempt = $this->detectMethodOverride($request);
            if ($overrideAttempt !== null) {
                $this->logSecurityEvent('blocked_method_override', $request, [
                    'original_method' => $method,
                    'override_attempt' => $overrideAttempt
                ]);
                return $this->createErrorResponse(400, 'Method override not allowed');
            }
        }

        // DEFENSE 3: Prevent body processing for bodyless methods
        if (in_array($method, self::BODYLESS_METHODS, true)) {
            $bodySize = $request->getBody()->getSize();
            if ($bodySize !== null && $bodySize > 0) {
                $this->logSecurityEvent('body_in_bodyless_method', $request, [
                    'method' => $method,
                    'body_size' => $bodySize
                ]);
                // Strip body for bodyless methods
                $request = $request->withBody(
                    \GuzzleHttp\Psr7\Utils::streamFor('')
                );
            }
        }

        // DEFENSE 4: Enforce Content-Type for methods with body
        if ($this->config['enforce_content_type']) {
            if (!in_array($method, self::BODYLESS_METHODS, true)) {
                $contentType = $request->getHeaderLine('Content-Type');
                if ($this->hasBody($request) && empty($contentType)) {
                    $this->logSecurityEvent('missing_content_type', $request, [
                        'method' => $method
                    ]);
                    return $this->createErrorResponse(415, 'Content-Type required');
                }
            }
        }

        // DEFENSE 5: Block TRACE method (potential XST attack)
        if ($method === 'TRACE') {
            $this->logSecurityEvent('blocked_trace_method', $request, []);
            return $this->createErrorResponse(405, 'TRACE method disabled');
        }

        // Add security headers to response
        $response = $handler->handle($request);

        return $response
            ->withHeader('X-Content-Type-Options', 'nosniff')
            ->withHeader('X-Frame-Options', 'DENY');
    }

    private function detectMethodOverride(ServerRequestInterface $request): ?string {
        // Check common method override headers and parameters
        $overrideIndicators = [
            'headers' => [
                'X-HTTP-Method-Override',
                'X-HTTP-Method',
                'X-Method-Override',
            ],
            'params' => [
                '_method',
                '__method',
                'method',
            ]
        ];

        // Check headers
        foreach ($overrideIndicators['headers'] as $header) {
            if ($request->hasHeader($header)) {
                return 'header:' . $header . '=' . $request->getHeaderLine($header);
            }
        }

        // Check query parameters
        $queryParams = $request->getQueryParams();
        foreach ($overrideIndicators['params'] as $param) {
            if (isset($queryParams[$param])) {
                return 'query:' . $param . '=' . $queryParams[$param];
            }
        }

        // Check body parameters (POST data)
        $bodyParams = $request->getParsedBody();
        if (is_array($bodyParams)) {
            foreach ($overrideIndicators['params'] as $param) {
                if (isset($bodyParams[$param])) {
                    return 'body:' . $param . '=' . $bodyParams[$param];
                }
            }
        }

        return null;
    }

    private function hasBody(ServerRequestInterface $request): bool {
        $body = $request->getBody();
        return $body->getSize() !== null && $body->getSize() > 0;
    }

    private function logSecurityEvent(
        string $event,
        ServerRequestInterface $request,
        array $context
    ): void {
        if (!$this->config['log_suspicious_requests']) {
            return;
        }

        $this->logger->warning('[HTTP_SECURITY] ' . $event, array_merge([
            'event' => $event,
            'ip' => $this->getClientIp($request),
            'uri' => (string) $request->getUri(),
            'user_agent' => $request->getHeaderLine('User-Agent'),
            'timestamp' => date('c'),
        ], $context));
    }

    private function getClientIp(ServerRequestInterface $request): string {
        $serverParams = $request->getServerParams();

        // Only trust X-Forwarded-For behind trusted proxy
        if (isset($serverParams['TRUSTED_PROXY']) && $serverParams['TRUSTED_PROXY']) {
            $forwarded = $request->getHeaderLine('X-Forwarded-For');
            if (!empty($forwarded)) {
                $ips = array_map('trim', explode(',', $forwarded));
                return $ips[0];
            }
        }

        return $serverParams['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown';
    }

    private function createErrorResponse(int $status, string $message): ResponseInterface {
        $response = new \GuzzleHttp\Psr7\Response($status);
        $body = json_encode([
            'error' => true,
            'message' => $message,
            'status' => $status
        ]);

        return $response
            ->withHeader('Content-Type', 'application/json')
            ->withHeader('Allow', implode(', ', self::ALLOWED_METHODS))
            ->withBody(\GuzzleHttp\Psr7\Utils::streamFor($body));
    }
}
```

**Route-Level Method Enforcement**:

```php
<?php
namespace App\Router;

class SecureRouter {
    private array $routes = [];

    public function addRoute(
        string $path,
        array $methods,
        callable $handler,
        array $middleware = []
    ): void {
        // Normalize and validate methods at registration time
        $methods = array_map('strtoupper', $methods);

        foreach ($methods as $method) {
            if (!in_array($method, ['GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'PATCH', 'DELETE'], true)) {
                throw new \InvalidArgumentException(
                    "Invalid HTTP method: {$method}"
                );
            }
        }

        $this->routes[$path] = [
            'methods' => $methods,
            'handler' => $handler,
            'middleware' => $middleware
        ];
    }

    public function dispatch(string $method, string $path): mixed {
        $method = strtoupper($method);

        if (!isset($this->routes[$path])) {
            http_response_code(404);
            return ['error' => 'Not found'];
        }

        $route = $this->routes[$path];

        // Strict method check at dispatch time
        if (!in_array($method, $route['methods'], true)) {
            http_response_code(405);
            header('Allow: ' . implode(', ', $route['methods']));
            return ['error' => 'Method not allowed'];
        }

        return call_user_func($route['handler']);
    }
}

// Usage example
$router = new SecureRouter();

// Route only accepts POST and DELETE
$router->addRoute('/api/users/{id}', ['POST', 'DELETE'], function() {
    // Handler logic
});
```

