**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- `allowExec=true` permits arbitrary command execution through SSI `#exec` directives
- `isVirtualWebappRelative=false` allows path traversal to access files outside the web root
- User-controlled input flows directly into SSI-processed content without sanitization
- Debug mode enabled in production leaks sensitive configuration information
- Mapping SSI to all `.html` files expands the attack surface unnecessarily

