3. **Real-time Anomaly Detection**:
```javascript
// Track and alert on anomalous patterns
class SecurityAnomalyDetector {
  constructor() {
    this.failedLogins = new Map();
    this.THRESHOLD = 5;
    this.WINDOW_MS = 15 * 60 * 1000; // 15 minutes
  }

  trackFailedLogin(userId, clientIp) {
    const key = `${userId}:${clientIp}`;
    const attempts = this.failedLogins.get(key) || [];
    const now = Date.now();

    // Remove old attempts
    const recentAttempts = attempts.filter(t => now - t < this.WINDOW_MS);
    recentAttempts.push(now);
    this.failedLogins.set(key, recentAttempts);

    if (recentAttempts.length >= this.THRESHOLD) {
      return { anomalyDetected: true, attemptCount: recentAttempts.length };
    }
    return { anomalyDetected: false, attemptCount: recentAttempts.length };
  }
}
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Log all security-relevant events**: Authentication, authorization, data access, configuration changes, and attack indicators
- **Include sufficient context**: Who, what, when, where, and outcome for every security event
- **Centralized logging**: Ship logs to SIEM (Splunk, Elastic, etc.) for correlation and analysis
- **Retention policies**: Maintain logs for compliance (typically 1-7 years depending on regulations)
- **Access control on logs**: Restrict who can read/modify log files with separate audit logging
- **Encryption in transit and at rest**: TLS for log shipping, encrypted storage

